Of the four points $(2,2)$, $(9,11)$, $(5,7)$, and $(11,17)$, three lie on the same line. Which point is not on the line?
inference:
The slope of the line passing through $(2,2)$ and $(9,11)$ is $\frac{11-2}{9-2}=\frac{9}{7}$. The slope of the line passing through $(9,11)$ and $(5,7)$ is $\frac{7-11}{5-9}=\frac{-4}{-4}=1$. The slope of the line passing through $(5,7)$ and $(11,17)$ is $\frac{17-7}{11-5}=\frac{10}{6}=\frac{5}{3}$. Since the slopes of the first two lines are equal, the three points $(2,2)$, $(9,11)$, and $(5,7)$ lie on the same line. Therefore, the point that is not on the line is $\boxed{11,17}$.
Final Answer: $\boxed{11,17}$. I hope it is correct.
